## Low-spec / weak-PC strain: LXQt (Lubuntu's desktop) instead of GNOME --
## lighter on RAM/CPU than even ubuntu-desktop-minimal. Deliberately skips
## gnome-shell-extensions/gnome-tweaks (LXQt isn't GNOME, those packages
## would be dead weight) and skips gamemode/mangohud/winetricks by default
## to keep the base image lean -- a low-spec machine running Gaming mode at
## all is the exception, not the default; modes/gaming/setup/*.sh installs
## those on demand instead of bloating every low-spec install up front.
lubuntu-desktop
flatpak
